the LATE VICTOR QUELCH 
Mr. David Chatters ( Athabasca , Ref. ) : 
Mr. Speaker , I rise in the House today to make amends to an oversight from many years gone by . 
Mr. Victor Quelch was a member of parliament from 1935 to 1958 . 
in those 23 years he served as Social Credit member for the constituency of Acadia in southern Alberta . 
he was a very well regarded member of this House and served many roles , including chief critic for finance , agriculture and fisheries . 
in 1950 he was appointed by Prime Minister St. Laurent to serve as an adviser on the Canadian staff to the United Nations Assembly . 
before entering politics Mr. Quelch served in World War I and received the Military Cross for bravery . 
a sense of duty to his country and its citizens guided Mr. Quelch ' s entire life , yet when he passed away in 1975 a tribute was never held in his honour in this House . 
although it is long overdue , I would like to acknowledge the service and dedication of Mr. Quelch . 
his contributions to Canada may be long past but they are certainly not forgotten . 
